`@PropertySource` annotation has to be used in conjunction with `@Configuration` annotation like so,

    @Configuration
    @PropertySource(value = { &quot;classpath:application.properties&quot; })
    public class ApplicationProperties {
    	...
    }

Adding `@Configuration` annotation would solve the issue in this case.

To be able to have `@Value` with placeholders resolved you need to register a [`PropertySourcesPlaceholderConfigurer`][1]. As this is a `BeanFactoryPostProcessor` it needs to be registered as a `static` bean so that it can be detected early on in the process. 

    @Bean
    public static PropertySourcesPlaceholderConfigurer placeholderConfigurer() {
         return new PropertySourcesPlaceholderConfigurer();
    }

[1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/beans/factory/config/PropertyPlaceholderConfigurer.html

