    A - B - D
        |
        C

When the code gets to node C, it finds no other vertices to go to: `v == -1`. What happens then, it clears C and goes back to B. That&#39;s all good. But, at B we only know where we came from (the stack contains `[A,B]`). Now it finds the first unvisited vertex, but that&#39;s C again!

What you need to, when you go up from C to B, then find the next vertex to visit. You need to list all adjacent in order. 

